AGL Energy Ltd, Fairfax Media Ltd. When disposing of various shareholdings, by complete oversight these shares were not sold as I understood had occurred. Upon learning of this oversight today, I have immediately corrected the record. I intend to dispose of these shares as soon as possible.

Disposed of shares in Woodside Petroleum Limited, held in my name, of which I was not previously aware. In 2003, the shares were transferred to me from my deceased mother's estate and registered at an office address in Sydney where I worked for a short period. As a result, I did not to the best of my knowledge receive any mail or contact relating to these shares and was not aware of their existence until recently. I was required to evidence my occupancy of this office address before my ownership of these shares could be confirmed;

The firm which purchased shares in Cisco Systems Inc in 2000 on my behalf has, to my concern, not been able to locate a record of these shares from its archive such that they cannot currently be disposed. I trust that this matter will be remedied as soon as possible;
Alinta Energy Limited, a company in which I had previously owned shares in my name before it was delisted, was included in my statement of registrable interests in error.
Disposed of shares held in my name in AGL Energy Limited, Fairfax Media Limited and Infigen Energy Limited, and placed a sell order for shares in 21st Century Fox;
Disposed of shares held in my name in Domain Holdings Limited which were granted to me as an eligible Fairfax Media shareholder by reason of a scheme of arrangement effective 22 November 2017;

Ten Network Holdings has, effective 24 November 2017, been removed from the ASX Official List pursuant to Listing rule 17.11 following the transfer of all the issued capital of the company to CBS International Television Australia Pty Ltd. As such, I no longer hold shares in Ten Network Holdings.

Advise that I was provided with a complimentary dinner and ticket to an evening session of the 2018 Australian Open, as part of a fundraising event for the Cottage by the Sea Foundation. I was invited to attend by the Foundation's patron, Mr Frank Costa AO OAM.
